  "prompt": "What exactly is 'pins and needles?",
  "response": "\"Pins and needles\" is a common term used to describe a tingling or prickling sensation that occurs when there is temporary compression or irritation of nerves. This sensation is medically referred to as paresthesia. It often happens when pressure is placed on a nerve, such as when a person sits or lies in an awkward position for an extended period, causing restricted blood flow to the affected area. When the pressure is relieved, and normal blood flow resumes, the nerves start to recover and send abnormal signals to the brain, leading to the tingling sensation. While usually harmless and temporary, persistent or frequent occurrences of pins and needles may require medical attention to rule out underlying conditions.",
